                                    <p>The tablet is inscribed on <rs type="texts" key="multiple" n=""/>
                                        <rs type="sides" key="opisthographic">both sides</rs>. It preserves two superimposed inscriptions on side A: 20A, in a fragmentary state, and, incised over it on the upper left part of the tablet, 19A. According to the editors of <bibl><ptr target="#IDodoneDVC"/></bibl>, 19A was inscribed after the tablet had been folded, thus occupying the space created by the fold on the left. Side B preserves one inscription (21B) and remnants of other, erased inscriptions.</p>
